# Task 3 - Project Workflow

## Overview

This task defines the complete workflow of the **OptiCrop: Smart Agricultural Production Optimization Engine**. It outlines the sequence of activities involved in developing an AI-powered crop recommendation system.

---

## Workflow Phases

### Epic 1 – Define Problem and Understanding

- Define agricultural problem
- Gather business requirements
- Conduct literature survey
- Analyze social and business impact

### Epic 2 – Data Collection and Analysis

- Download dataset
- Import libraries
- Read dataset
- Univariate analysis
- Bivariate analysis
- Multivariate analysis

### Epic 3 – Data Preprocessing

- Check null values
- Handle outliers
- Extract seasonal crops
- Split training and testing data

### Epic 4 – Model Building

- K-Means Clustering
- Logistic Regression
- Evaluate model performance
- Save best model
- Predict suitable crop

### Epic 5 – Application Building

- Develop HTML frontend
- Build Flask backend
- Run and test application

---

## Technologies Used

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-learn
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Flask
- HTML
- CSS

---

## Outcome

The project workflow provides a structured roadmap for successfully implementing the OptiCrop Smart Agricultural Production Optimization Engine from problem definition to application deployment.
